featured_reviews.review_id: Eidgah or Idgah, also Eid Gah or Id Gah (Persian: `ydgh "site of Eid [observances]"; Bengali: iidgaah; Punjabi: `yd ghUrdu: `yd gh; Hindi: iidgaah) is a term used in South Asian Islamic culture for the open-air enclosure usually outside the city (or at the outskirts) reserved for Eid prayers offered in the morning of Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha.
